00:27:41,540 --> 00:27:43,967
- Are you serious?
- Yes, I am.

523
00:27:44,050 --> 00:27:47,622
We just have to find a way
that doesn't hurt Helena's public image.

524
00:27:48,422 --> 00:27:50,907
And I... I don't know how to say this.

525
00:27:50,990 --> 00:27:52,037
You already asked me that,

526
00:27:52,120 --> 00:27:54,367
I don't know what to tell you
to tell you or advise you.

527
00:27:54,450 --> 00:27:56,787
Well, you spend every week
advising strangers

528
00:27:56,870 --> 00:27:59,147
always something true, precise, subtle,

529
00:27:59,230 --> 00:28:01,297
and you can't say
a few words to your best friend?

530
00:28:01,380 --> 00:28:03,557
It's not like that when it comes to you.

531
00:28:03,640 --> 00:28:05,539
I respond to strangers.

532
00:28:05,622 --> 00:28:08,197
And I still don't understand
why you would do something so stupid.

533
00:28:08,280 --> 00:28:09,917
- Well, I'll give you the reasons why.
- Go ahead.

534
00:28:10,000 --> 00:28:13,197
First of all, I'm in the public eye now,
including physically.

535
00:28:13,280 --> 00:28:16,594
Second, she's talking crap
about male emotional emancipation.

536
00:28:17,250 --> 00:28:19,437
Third, I do everything
that a mom should do.

537
00:28:19,520 --> 00:28:21,219
I have seven more of these items, shall I continue?

538
00:28:21,302 --> 00:28:23,117
No, what's the problem,
embarrassed to be a "pama"?

539
00:28:23,200 --> 00:28:24,287
No, don't say that word,

540
00:28:24,370 --> 00:28:26,517
"pama" is a sexist expression.

541
00:28:26,600 --> 00:28:28,767
I said that once
and I fought with Helena for three days.

542
00:28:28,850 --> 00:28:30,017
I'm a father.

543
00:28:30,100 --> 00:28:33,297
And it's not about what I do,
it's about what I don't do anymore,

544
00:28:33,380 --> 00:28:35,128
starting with sex, that's four,

545
00:28:35,211 --> 00:28:38,267
and, from a prostate perspective,
that can't be underestimated either.

546
00:28:38,350 --> 00:28:39,897
Fifth, I'm not a husband anymore.

547
00:28:39,980 --> 00:28:43,047
Sixth, I'm no longer a teacher,
which has serious consequences.

548
00:28:43,130 --> 00:28:45,642
Seven, that the students don't know
who Italo Calvino is.

549
00:28:45,725 --> 00:28:47,402
Now do you understand my situation?

550
00:28:47,485 --> 00:28:48,485
Here you go.

551
00:28:50,422 --> 00:28:51,440
Listen, Humberto.

552
00:28:52,000 --> 00:28:55,277
If you could anonymously
ask Helena about your relationship,

553
00:28:55,360 --> 00:28:56,817
what would you ask?

554
00:28:56,900 --> 00:28:58,705
I don't get it, what do you mean?

555
00:28:58,788 --> 00:29:02,287
If you could
get her to confess something,

556
00:29:02,370 --> 00:29:05,139
not knowing that she's admitting it to you.

557
00:29:05,222 --> 00:29:08,377
Like, if she's cheating on you
or if she still loves you, I don't know.

558
00:29:08,460 --> 00:29:09,817
What would you ask?

559
00:29:10,320 --> 00:29:12,365
Tommaso, I don't understand shit.

560
00:29:13,250 --> 00:29:14,834
Well, I'd ask Ellena....

561
00:29:15,960 --> 00:29:17,371
I'd ask her if she was happy.

562
00:29:18,700 --> 00:29:20,411
Or unhappy, as I am now.

563
00:29:25,680 --> 00:29:27,887
The problem with the fourth mission.

564
00:29:27,970 --> 00:29:29,687
And on top of all the glitches,

565
00:29:29,770 --> 00:29:33,507
the fact that you can so easily
to kill your playmate is, uh.

566
00:29:33,590 --> 00:29:34,787
Yes, that's right, in connection with this.....

567
00:29:34,870 --> 00:29:37,197
No, there should at least be
the controller vibrating.

568
00:29:37,280 --> 00:29:38,537
But what we wanted to do, Zoya.

569
00:29:38,620 --> 00:29:40,537
We have to make it more unstable, okay?

570
00:29:41,840 --> 00:29:44,317
We're a few days away from the 27th,

571
00:29:44,400 --> 00:29:45,820
and I want to meet you.

572
00:29:46,330 --> 00:29:47,485
You want to play a game?

573
00:29:52,120 --> 00:29:53,897
I work with games.

574
00:29:53,980 --> 00:29:55,794
So it all depends on the game.

575
00:30:04,800 --> 00:30:07,188
Write me something
that you hate about him.

576
00:30:19,565 --> 00:30:20,685
It's a beautiful song, isn't it?

577
00:30:37,188 --> 00:30:38,787
- Esther!
- Hey!

578
00:30:38,870 --> 00:30:40,477
- Hey!
- How are you, sister?

579
00:30:40,560 --> 00:30:42,937
- Hello, daughter-in-law!
- Hello, son-in-law.

580
00:30:43,020 --> 00:30:44,534
- Flavio!
- So, how are you?

581
00:30:44,617 --> 00:30:45,857
- How's your stomach?
- It's good.

582
00:30:45,940 --> 00:30:47,857
- Brother-in-law?
- Yes!

583
00:30:47,940 --> 00:30:48,940
Here I am.

584
00:30:49,520 --> 00:30:50,657
Tell the truth,

585
00:30:50,740 --> 00:30:53,547
did it make you happy that I asked you
to help us move today?

586
00:30:53,630 --> 00:30:55,414
It's like waking up on your day off and saying:

587
00:30:55,497 --> 00:30:58,537
"What would be wacky this morning?
A good move."

588
00:30:58,620 --> 00:31:00,877
Relax, I've got it all done.

589
00:31:00,960 --> 00:31:03,165
- All that's left is the light stuff.
- Yeah, I can see that.

590
00:31:04,100 --> 00:31:06,125
- Hey, what about Abel?
- Hands up!

591
00:31:07,565 --> 00:31:10,467
- Who is it?
- Now you're gonna help me pack!

592
00:31:10,550 --> 00:31:12,717
Okay, your uncle will help you pack,

593
00:31:12,800 --> 00:31:15,691
but first I have to
help my dad carry the boxes.

594
00:31:16,540 --> 00:31:17,457
All right?

595
00:31:17,540 --> 00:31:18,540
Bye, sweetie!

596
00:31:22,970 --> 00:31:24,527
How's the apartment search going?

597
00:31:24,610 --> 00:31:25,467
All right. (chuckles)

598
00:31:25,550 --> 00:31:27,327
I'm looking, and Zoya says no.

599
00:31:27,410 --> 00:31:28,287
Are you talking to me?

600
00:31:28,370 --> 00:31:30,007
Esther drove me crazy looking for a house.

601
00:31:30,090 --> 00:31:31,107
Yes...

602
00:31:31,190 --> 00:31:32,337
He doesn't drive.

603
00:31:32,420 --> 00:31:34,907
He hates driving,
so I have to drive myself.

604
00:31:34,990 --> 00:31:36,571
Dump a man if he doesn't drive?

605
00:31:37,110 --> 00:31:38,110
Drives what?

606
00:31:40,091 --> 00:31:42,251
No, that's okay. I'm gonna go get other things.

607
00:31:46,550 --> 00:31:49,147
Two: hair, everywhere.

608
00:31:49,230 --> 00:31:52,011
You should have seen the bathroom after he shaved.

609
00:31:53,850 --> 00:31:57,862
Three, he's 43 years old,
and he still dresses like a 20-year-old.

610
00:32:03,120 --> 00:32:06,182
Fourth, he only listens
only to depressing music.

611
00:32:14,708 --> 00:32:17,787
Five: "I don't care."
He always says that.

612
00:32:17,870 --> 00:32:19,237
He never offers anything.

613
00:32:19,320 --> 00:32:22,707
Restaurants, trips, movies--
it's always me.

614
00:32:22,790 --> 00:32:24,868
But you like to organize things.

615
00:32:30,034 --> 00:32:33,600
Six: he still hasn't learned
how to say my name.

616
00:32:35,610 --> 00:32:37,767
Seven: he's stupid.

617
00:32:37,850 --> 00:32:41,277
His new novel is out of print
because he won't change the ending.

618
00:32:41,360 --> 00:32:43,197
"Commercial" is a terrible word for him.

619
00:32:43,280 --> 00:32:44,697
I asked for one thing...

620
00:32:45,500 --> 00:32:46,500
Tom?

621
00:32:53,740 --> 00:32:54,867
Are you done?

622
00:32:54,950 --> 00:32:56,902
No, we just started...

623
00:32:58,980 --> 00:32:59,897
Thank you.

624
00:32:59,980 --> 00:33:02,617
- Abel, your skateboard.
- Yeah, Dad.

625
00:33:03,910 --> 00:33:06,227
It's just scary to see a house like this.

626
00:33:06,310 --> 00:33:07,437
You bet...

627
00:33:07,520 --> 00:33:08,547
Then...

628
00:33:08,630 --> 00:33:11,567
Everything's gone to hell with this move.

629
00:33:11,650 --> 00:33:13,588
- These are your things.
- My stuff?

630
00:33:14,540 --> 00:33:15,577
There's an essay.

631
00:33:17,070 --> 00:33:18,367
Mom's letter?

632
00:33:18,450 --> 00:33:19,725
Mom's letter, yeah.

633
00:33:23,250 --> 00:33:24,251
Oh my god...

634
00:33:25,440 --> 00:33:27,280
Need to write again, my goodness....

635
00:33:29,850 --> 00:33:32,262
Actually, I don't think
it's irreparable.

636
00:33:34,228 --> 00:33:36,731
Eighth, I'm no longer happy
with him around.

637
00:33:37,330 --> 00:33:40,822
Nine: Maybe
I just forgot how to be happy.

638
00:33:41,634 --> 00:33:43,622
Tenth: I don't know.

639
00:34:06,720 --> 00:34:10,148
- You okay?
- Yeah, just... a little tired.

640
00:34:11,817 --> 00:34:12,817
Look, uh.

641
00:34:13,880 --> 00:34:14,817
I'll drive.

642
00:34:14,900 --> 00:34:16,537
No, no, I'll drive.

643
00:34:16,620 --> 00:34:18,287
No, I'll drive, you park.

644
00:34:18,370 --> 00:34:19,370
It's fine.

645
00:34:47,400 --> 00:34:50,697
I haven't told her yet.
I'm waiting for the right time.

646
00:34:51,314 --> 00:34:53,105
- Help me!
- Again?

647
00:34:53,188 --> 00:34:54,497
Umberto, think carefully.

648
00:34:54,580 --> 00:34:57,917
You know, breaking up
after all these years is crazy!

649
00:34:58,000 --> 00:35:01,387
- It's gonna be hard, it's gonna be sad.
- Well, I already know that.

650
00:35:01,470 --> 00:35:03,787
You'll have to box up the books,

651
00:35:03,870 --> 00:35:06,537
fighting over CDs: "That's mine!
- No, it's yours..."

652
00:35:06,620 --> 00:35:07,837
Sharing photos... How?

653
00:35:07,920 --> 00:35:10,767
Official photos,
I'm always in the back, out of focus, okay.

654
00:35:10,850 --> 00:35:14,111
Why don't you think about
about the good things between you two?

655
00:35:14,194 --> 00:35:15,897
Well, why don't you just focus on work?

656
00:35:15,980 --> 00:35:17,337
At work? Look!

657
00:35:17,420 --> 00:35:19,747
- We're alone, no one's here.
- Of course, everyone's in class.

658
00:35:19,830 --> 00:35:22,627
Of course you are,
the kids are in class and I'm in the hallway!

659
00:35:22,710 --> 00:35:24,577
I've been sent to the reserve,
I was marginalized.

660
00:35:24,660 --> 00:35:26,897
- You know, me!
- They made you deputy director!

661
00:35:26,980 --> 00:35:29,607
Exactly, also a mockery,
because it's the eighth:

662
00:35:29,690 --> 00:35:32,387
not only am I unable to teach
because of administrative duties,

663
00:35:32,470 --> 00:35:34,454
but, uh, the ninth:
According to the department head,

664
00:35:34,537 --> 00:35:38,127
a man in my position
can't just be a teacher, okay?

665
00:35:38,210 --> 00:35:41,117
Me, who's used to being on the front lines!
I've been killed!

666
00:35:41,200 --> 00:35:42,537
How much did I weigh three years ago?

667
00:35:42,620 --> 00:35:44,434
Only 120 kilos! Do you understand?

668
00:35:46,900 --> 00:35:48,548
- What?
- There's no tenth item.

669
00:35:49,090 --> 00:35:50,100
Tenth...

670
00:35:50,710 --> 00:35:52,947
Yes? Ah, here, come here, Laruffa.

671
00:35:53,030 --> 00:35:54,297
How's the new teacher?

672
00:35:54,380 --> 00:35:55,782
Have we passed Calvino yet?

673
00:35:56,370 --> 00:35:57,430
Who, teacher?

674
00:35:58,548 --> 00:36:00,194
Number ten. Go on, go.

675
00:36:01,100 --> 00:36:02,514
And this is one of the best.

676
00:36:07,908 --> 00:36:08,908
Hi.

677
00:36:09,550 --> 00:36:10,934
What's the music?

678
00:36:11,017 --> 00:36:12,140
It lifts your spirits.

679
00:36:12,902 --> 00:36:14,067
What are you doing?

680
00:36:14,150 --> 00:36:16,267
Working on a new ending for the novel.

681
00:36:16,350 --> 00:36:17,897
- You did?
- Yeah.

682
00:36:19,630 --> 00:36:21,394
As usual, the fridge is empty.

683
00:36:22,350 --> 00:36:25,211
- I'm gonna order some food, okay?
- I ordered a Syrian restaurant.

684
00:36:27,314 --> 00:36:28,320
For 9:00 p.m.

685
00:36:29,640 --> 00:36:30,640
All right. Uh-huh.

686
00:36:38,685 --> 00:36:40,137
- You like it?
- I do.

687
00:36:41,211 --> 00:36:42,677
Good evening, may I leave a menu?

688
00:36:42,760 --> 00:36:44,147
Of course, thank you.

689
00:36:44,230 --> 00:36:45,459
No, no, wait.

690
00:36:45,542 --> 00:36:46,467
This way...

691
00:36:46,550 --> 00:36:48,387
- Mustabal...
- Yes.

692
00:36:48,470 --> 00:36:51,437
Taratura Aleppo,
full Damascus and Fattoush for two.

693
00:36:51,520 --> 00:36:52,731
- That's great.
- Uh, thank you.

694
00:36:55,074 --> 00:36:57,051
Well, I already looked it up online.

695
00:36:59,000 --> 00:37:00,011
No, wait.

696
00:37:00,628 --> 00:37:01,628
I'll give it a shot.

697
00:37:03,230 --> 00:37:04,087
No.

698
00:37:04,170 --> 00:37:05,200
You take one of them,

699
00:37:05,850 --> 00:37:08,034
then you put this in there.

700
00:37:11,737 --> 00:37:12,737
Try it!

701
00:37:14,205 --> 00:37:15,597
I've been thinking.

702
00:37:15,680 --> 00:37:17,677
It's been a long time since we've been away for a weekend.

703
00:37:17,760 --> 00:37:19,137
We were recently in Tuscany.

704
00:37:19,220 --> 00:37:21,127
I mean alone,

705
00:37:21,210 --> 00:37:23,200
without the whole horde of friends.

706
00:37:24,811 --> 00:37:25,847
I don't know if I can.

707
00:37:25,930 --> 00:37:28,308
We have a project to deliver and we're behind.

708
00:37:28,971 --> 00:37:32,137
I don't have time
to find a hotel, buy tickets.

709
00:37:32,220 --> 00:37:33,394
Maybe I can.

710
00:37:35,180 --> 00:37:36,948
- Where do you want to go?
- Prague.

711
00:37:37,737 --> 00:37:38,637
Paris...

712
00:37:38,720 --> 00:37:41,097
Places where couples go
barely start dating.

713
00:37:41,980 --> 00:37:43,908
Or where couples who are in crisis go.

714
00:37:45,440 --> 00:37:46,685
Beautiful cutlets!

715
00:37:53,748 --> 00:37:56,080
The more distant I get, the cuter he gets.

716
00:37:56,754 --> 00:37:58,207
This is awkward.

717
00:37:58,290 --> 00:38:00,417
It's easier to start a war than to end it.

718
00:38:00,500 --> 00:38:01,787
You've been through this?

719
00:38:01,870 --> 00:38:03,927
How do you know all this?

720
00:38:04,010 --> 00:38:06,397
Because I'm Gabriel Garcia Marquez.

721
00:38:06,480 --> 00:38:09,437
Need I remind you that you're corresponding
with a famous dead writer.

722
00:38:09,520 --> 00:38:10,797
Ironic, too.

723
00:38:10,880 --> 00:38:13,185
I hope you're at least not ugly.

724
00:38:13,268 --> 00:38:14,268
Maybe.

725
00:38:14,750 --> 00:38:15,851
What kind of guy are you?

726
00:38:18,160 --> 00:38:19,160
I'll tell you myself.

727
00:38:19,611 --> 00:38:21,737
You seem rough, but you're fragile.

728
00:38:21,820 --> 00:38:24,107
And when you're fragile, you get rude.

729
00:38:24,190 --> 00:38:26,557
You pick the wine, you pay the bill.

730
00:38:26,640 --> 00:38:28,157
and you know how to cheat.

731
00:38:28,240 --> 00:38:29,240
Maybe.

732
00:38:31,070 --> 00:38:32,285
You think I'm weird?

733
00:38:33,977 --> 00:38:35,379
I think you...

734
00:38:35,462 --> 00:38:36,462
original.

735
00:38:38,297 --> 00:38:39,707
I'm sorry!

736
00:38:39,790 --> 00:38:40,877
Whoever it is,

737
00:38:40,960 --> 00:38:44,197
he has to stop shaving in the bathroom.

738
00:38:44,280 --> 00:38:46,127
First of all, it's not your house,

739
00:38:46,210 --> 00:38:48,517
and when there's hair everywhere, I can't stand it.

740
00:38:48,600 --> 00:38:49,600
Okay?

741
00:38:49,630 --> 00:38:50,640
Thank you.

742
00:38:51,200 --> 00:38:53,217
- I like it, what do you think?
- "My girlfriend..."

743
00:38:53,300 --> 00:38:57,245
- That's the guy with the sock in his mouth!
- I must have made a mistake, it was from below.

744
00:39:02,320 --> 00:39:03,348
Why are you here?

745
00:39:04,754 --> 00:39:05,754
There was no business.

746
00:39:06,720 --> 00:39:08,137
Do you want to go for a walk?

747
00:39:08,982 --> 00:39:10,194
A walk?

748
00:39:11,462 --> 00:39:13,051
We live in Rome and we never walk.

749
00:39:14,182 --> 00:39:15,527
Where do you want to go?

750
00:39:15,610 --> 00:39:17,097
It's been a rough day.

751
00:39:17,180 --> 00:39:19,611
We'll take a walk while standing still.

752
00:39:20,880 --> 00:39:22,274
Stop joking around.

753
00:39:24,034 --> 00:39:25,520
I'm not kidding, Zoya.

754
00:39:26,697 --> 00:39:28,594
Kidding.

755
00:39:29,417 --> 00:39:30,514
Zo-e.

756
00:39:31,611 --> 00:39:32,705
Zoé.

757
00:39:32,788 --> 00:39:34,447
I can't say it.

758
00:39:34,530 --> 00:39:36,411
I get "F" for "Foe."

759
00:39:37,165 --> 00:39:39,717
- It's difficult.
- Tongue between teeth...

760
00:39:39,800 --> 00:39:43,188
If it's between the teeth, it's "Dzoe."

761
00:40:04,240 --> 00:40:05,240
Thank you.

762
