00:40:37,690 --> 00:40:40,177
Now I have to ride a bike,
and I hate bikes!

768
00:40:40,260 --> 00:40:42,517
Umberto, you can't
always complain about everything!

769
00:40:42,600 --> 00:40:46,147
Tommaso, I have hemorrhoids,
so I have the right to complain!

770
00:40:46,230 --> 00:40:48,637
Helena made me do it,
she started a campaign for bike lanes

771
00:40:48,720 --> 00:40:51,997
and he says, "You can't be photographed
in the car again."

772
00:40:52,080 --> 00:40:53,287
But there's no way in hell I'm ditching the car!

773
00:40:53,370 --> 00:40:55,677
Compromise is normal for a couple.

774
00:40:55,760 --> 00:40:58,337
You can change a little for her, can't you?

775
00:40:58,420 --> 00:41:00,547
A little? Tommaso, I'm a different person,

776
00:41:00,630 --> 00:41:03,497
You've known me for 25 years,
was I like this in college?

777
00:41:03,580 --> 00:41:05,837
Yeah, in college.
we used to call you poor thing.

778
00:41:05,920 --> 00:41:07,377
Para-param, para-param, para-param,

779
00:41:07,460 --> 00:41:09,777
Para-para-para-pam-pam-pam, I screwed up!

780
00:41:09,860 --> 00:41:12,567
I remember, but that's exactly why
she fell in love:

781
00:41:12,650 --> 00:41:15,217
for my witty remarks
that got me in trouble.

782
00:41:15,300 --> 00:41:18,057
She laughed, sometimes to the point of tears.

783
00:41:18,140 --> 00:41:19,747
And now he's terrorizing me.

784
00:41:19,830 --> 00:41:22,788
Now before I talk,
I have to count to five thousand!

785
00:41:23,680 --> 00:41:24,742
Then it's easy.

786
00:41:26,010 --> 00:41:27,010
Don't count anymore.

787
00:41:27,040 --> 00:41:29,997
Don't give up your witty
your witty remarks, be like you were in your 20s.

788
00:41:30,080 --> 00:41:32,411
Maybe then she'll stop
to tolerate you.

789
00:41:33,188 --> 00:41:35,405
How did it occur to you
to show up like that?

790
00:41:36,205 --> 00:41:37,207
Convenient.

791
00:41:37,290 --> 00:41:39,520
No one asked you
to dress uncomfortable but clean!

792
00:41:40,080 --> 00:41:42,331
Ah, just a coffee stain....

793
00:41:42,960 --> 00:41:44,845
During the anthem, I'll put my hand over my heart....

794
00:41:45,470 --> 00:41:47,040
Is this a matter of etiquette?

795
00:41:47,630 --> 00:41:49,254
No, it's a rag question.

796
00:41:49,337 --> 00:41:50,970
Not etiquette, hygiene.

797
00:41:51,748 --> 00:41:52,927
You're a formalist, Héléna.

798
00:41:53,010 --> 00:41:56,017
I'm not Helena here, I'm the mayor, and you're my...

799
00:41:56,100 --> 00:41:58,788
I'm not, I'm always Umberto.

800
00:42:07,470 --> 00:42:08,888
This way, this way, please!

801
00:42:08,971 --> 00:42:10,480
- The picture's from here!
- Mayor!

802
00:42:11,394 --> 00:42:12,394
One more shot!

803
00:42:12,420 --> 00:42:13,926
- Thank you!
- Look here, please!

804
00:42:13,950 --> 00:42:15,867
- Please take a look at this!
- Thank you.

805
00:42:15,950 --> 00:42:17,782
Please stand during the national anthem!

806
00:42:21,702 --> 00:42:23,557
- Please.
- Yes, I am.

807
00:42:23,640 --> 00:42:25,647
- Good luck, guys.
- Thank you.

808
00:42:25,730 --> 00:42:27,287
It was just a joke, Héléna.

809
00:42:27,370 --> 00:42:29,848
Don't you realize
that we're gonna be all over the papers tomorrow?

810
00:42:29,931 --> 00:42:31,497
I will be destroyed.

811
00:42:31,580 --> 00:42:33,017
How can you say that?

812
00:42:33,100 --> 00:42:34,674
We're already in a crisis!

813
00:42:35,530 --> 00:42:38,057
- Are we in crisis?
- Of course we're in crisis.

814
00:42:39,340 --> 00:42:42,057
The coalition has disintegrated, all the polls are against....

815
00:42:42,140 --> 00:42:43,871
We're hanging by a thread.

816
00:42:43,954 --> 00:42:45,037
Is that funny?

817
00:42:45,120 --> 00:42:46,027
What's so funny?

818
00:42:46,110 --> 00:42:47,665
You laughed at my jokes once!

819
00:42:47,748 --> 00:42:50,017
Once! Not twice or thrice!

820
00:42:50,100 --> 00:42:52,247
In fact, for what it's worth,

821
00:42:52,330 --> 00:42:55,137
you were once proud of me for being in politics.

822
00:42:55,220 --> 00:42:57,527
- Listen, uh.
- Can someone help me with my homework?

823
00:42:57,610 --> 00:42:59,725
- Yeah, baby. Now.
- Yes, baby. Daddy's gonna help.

824
00:43:07,794 --> 00:43:09,777
Yesterday was a good day.

825
00:43:09,860 --> 00:43:11,131
Things have gotten better,

826
00:43:11,820 --> 00:43:13,245
and I'm thinking about leaving him.

827
00:43:13,890 --> 00:43:15,360
It's all so weird.

828
00:43:16,570 --> 00:43:17,748
Do you feel guilty?

829
00:43:23,410 --> 00:43:25,357
He gave no reason to hurt him,

830
00:43:25,440 --> 00:43:28,400
but sometimes I feel like I'm betraying him.

831
00:43:30,800 --> 00:43:31,954
Did you cheat on him?

832
00:43:38,365 --> 00:43:39,365
Yes.

833
00:43:44,045 --> 00:43:45,302
You really cheated?

834
00:43:46,400 --> 00:43:49,051
A long time ago, but it has nothing to do
with this crisis.

835
00:43:54,670 --> 00:43:56,114
- Zoya!
- What?

836
00:43:59,400 --> 00:44:00,960
I'm gonna go take out the trash.

837
00:44:01,580 --> 00:44:02,580
All right. Uh-huh.

838
00:44:12,777 --> 00:44:15,477
Anyway, he was cheating on me, too,

839
00:44:15,560 --> 00:44:17,142
but I didn't tell him I knew it.

840
00:44:22,091 --> 00:44:23,467
Why didn't you tell him?

841
00:44:23,550 --> 00:44:25,177
There was no problem between us.

842
00:44:25,931 --> 00:44:26,937
It happens.

843
00:44:28,902 --> 00:44:31,565
- Why'd you do it?
- It happens.

844
00:44:36,034 --> 00:44:38,502
I was suddenly terrified
at the thought of losing him.

845
00:44:49,325 --> 00:44:50,325
Are you coming to bed?

846
00:44:50,940 --> 00:44:52,477
I'll write for a while and then I'll come back.

847
00:44:52,560 --> 00:44:53,560
All right. Uh-huh.

848
00:45:10,490 --> 00:45:12,697
- Nina, coffee, please.
- Right away.

849
00:45:15,097 --> 00:45:18,387
Speaking of the production bonus:
give my bonus to the guys.

850
00:45:18,470 --> 00:45:21,047
I'm sure they'll be able
to achieve three percent development.

851
00:45:21,130 --> 00:45:22,130
Suit yourself.

852
00:45:23,200 --> 00:45:24,548
London called,

853
00:45:25,131 --> 00:45:27,207
want to expedite your arrival.

854
00:45:27,290 --> 00:45:29,120
We'll announce it in five days.

855
00:45:31,760 --> 00:45:33,997
I thought I had a few more weeks.

856
00:45:34,080 --> 00:45:35,162
Why?

857
00:45:35,245 --> 00:45:36,454
You want to change your mind?

858
00:45:36,537 --> 00:45:38,068
No, no, no, no.

859
00:45:38,857 --> 00:45:41,428
But...I have some things I need to take care of.

860
00:45:43,108 --> 00:45:44,125
Handle it.

861
00:45:45,870 --> 00:45:46,917
Tom?

862
00:45:47,000 --> 00:45:49,517
Where are we going so elegant?

863
00:45:49,600 --> 00:45:50,640
Surprise!

864
00:45:51,190 --> 00:45:53,245
Listen, do you know how to tie this thing?

865
00:45:53,800 --> 00:45:54,800
Which one?

866
00:45:56,310 --> 00:45:57,542
Is that the surprise?

867
00:45:59,062 --> 00:46:00,157
Why?

868
00:46:00,240 --> 00:46:01,117
Bad?

869
00:46:01,200 --> 00:46:04,407
No, but I've never
seen you dressed like that.

870
00:46:04,490 --> 00:46:05,490
All right. Uh-huh.

871
00:46:05,565 --> 00:46:07,157
There's always a first time.

872
00:46:07,240 --> 00:46:08,477
Can you come here for a minute?

873
00:46:08,560 --> 00:46:10,967
- I have something important to tell you.
- Zoya, we're late.

874
00:46:11,050 --> 00:46:13,554
I'll take the car and wait downstairs,
hurry up, get dressed.

875
00:46:16,205 --> 00:46:17,680
Are you gonna tell me where we're going?

876
00:46:18,290 --> 00:46:19,851
You go on in, I'll park.

877
00:46:55,480 --> 00:46:58,537
Good evening, everyone,
and welcome to the presentation,

878
00:46:58,620 --> 00:47:00,217
after years of waiting,

879
00:47:00,300 --> 00:47:03,714
Tommaso Rosso's third, new novel.

880
00:47:06,780 --> 00:47:10,777
I'd like to first read to you
a quote from the beginning of my book.

881
00:47:15,702 --> 00:47:19,402
"In that moment, there was nothing
"but quiet happiness.

882
00:47:19,485 --> 00:47:22,677
But he would have preferred mature unhappiness

883
00:47:22,760 --> 00:47:25,474
that smooth glide,
no bumps, no waves,

884
00:47:26,020 --> 00:47:27,257
without storms,

885
00:47:27,810 --> 00:47:30,525
"like a giant ship
stuck in a pool."

886
00:47:34,422 --> 00:47:37,987
Are you saying you don't believe
in your romantic ending?

887
00:47:38,070 --> 00:47:41,267
I know in novels, the author determines the ending,

888
00:47:41,350 --> 00:47:43,268
as opposed to what happens in life.

889
00:48:36,750 --> 00:48:38,365
There's another surprise.

890
00:48:39,028 --> 00:48:40,467
Another one?

891
00:48:40,550 --> 00:48:43,074
- We're going to see a house.
- Now?

892
00:48:44,240 --> 00:48:45,240
Now.

893
00:48:48,342 --> 00:48:50,847
- Okay.
- This house is for sale.

894
00:48:50,930 --> 00:48:53,542
It's smaller, but I think it's, uh,
it's perfect for us.

895
00:48:54,137 --> 00:48:55,257
So...

896
00:48:57,060 --> 00:48:58,685
Wait...

897
00:48:59,780 --> 00:49:01,288
Momentum...

898
00:49:01,371 --> 00:49:02,371
Can you see anything?

899
00:49:02,450 --> 00:49:03,807
- Yeah. (chuckles)
- Uh-huh?

900
00:49:03,890 --> 00:49:04,937
Okay...

901
00:49:05,870 --> 00:49:06,870
Here we go.

902
00:49:07,417 --> 00:49:08,605
This is the living room.

903
00:49:10,331 --> 00:49:11,565
Look at the terrace!

904
00:49:12,114 --> 00:49:13,462
You can see all of Rome from here.

905
00:49:15,862 --> 00:49:18,045
There's the kitchen-dining room.

906
00:49:19,240 --> 00:49:24,354
And here at the end,
there's an extra room, just in case.

907
00:49:24,982 --> 00:49:27,028
Look, open-beam ceiling.

908
00:49:28,040 --> 00:49:29,257
Isn't that a miracle?

909
00:49:30,720 --> 00:49:32,411
And here...

910
00:49:35,640 --> 00:49:37,325
It's a bedroom

911
00:49:38,650 --> 00:49:40,491
with a panoramic window.

912
00:49:42,080 --> 00:49:43,142
Look at the light!

913
00:49:45,910 --> 00:49:46,971
Wonderful...

914
00:51:01,405 --> 00:51:02,765
We made love.

915
00:51:03,805 --> 00:51:05,474
I'm pretty sure I don't love him anymore.

916
00:51:06,548 --> 00:51:08,194
How am I supposed to tell him now?

917
00:51:09,885 --> 00:51:11,057
CHAPTER FIVE: ACCETTA

918
00:51:11,140 --> 00:51:14,305
OF THE MEANING OF THE WORD "ACCEPT" -
ACCEPT THAT THIS IS THE WAY IT SHOULD BE

919
00:51:14,388 --> 00:51:16,042
EXAMPLE: ACCEPT REALITY

920
00:51:16,125 --> 00:51:18,362
OR: "HATCHET" - A SMALL AXE

921
00:51:18,445 --> 00:51:20,470
EXAMPLE: HATCHET

922
00:51:23,290 --> 00:51:25,325
Ellena realized something was wrong.

923
00:51:26,034 --> 00:51:29,562
The party realized she was in crisis,
and they called me and asked me to support her,

924
00:51:29,645 --> 00:51:33,417
because they're afraid that her anxiety
will affect the council's position.

925
00:51:33,500 --> 00:51:34,822
They're afraid she'll drop everything.

926
00:51:35,660 --> 00:51:36,660
Are you listening?

927
00:51:37,782 --> 00:51:38,782
Yeah, yeah.

928
00:51:39,474 --> 00:51:42,385
You thought it was as easy
as closing a company?

929
00:51:42,468 --> 00:51:44,320
It's about people, Umberto.

930
00:51:44,890 --> 00:51:46,857
But when something is over, it's over.

931
00:51:47,428 --> 00:51:50,607
It's like... putting a Band-Aid on a wound.

932
00:51:50,690 --> 00:51:53,748
I had just decided
to tell her everything tonight, even, uh.

933
00:51:54,280 --> 00:51:56,717
I wrote another non-harmful speech....

934
00:51:56,800 --> 00:51:57,800
May I?

935
00:51:59,790 --> 00:52:00,790
Let's hear it.

936
00:52:03,291 --> 00:52:04,291
"Beloved,

937
00:52:05,230 --> 00:52:08,437
everything I've felt for you
all these years, I can't describe.

938
00:52:08,520 --> 00:52:10,070
I asked the poets for help.

939
00:52:11,030 --> 00:52:13,631
"I must have climbed a million stairs
I descended by giving you my hand..."

940
00:52:13,714 --> 00:52:15,037
Wait, Umberto.

941
00:52:15,120 --> 00:52:17,017
First of all, Héléna is not dead.

942
00:52:17,100 --> 00:52:18,637
So you want to break up with her,

943
00:52:18,720 --> 00:52:21,174
starting with a declaration of love,
quoting Montale?

944
00:52:21,257 --> 00:52:22,099
Why.

945
00:52:22,182 --> 00:52:24,970
Why don't you tell the truth,
why don't you tell the goddamn truth?

946
00:52:26,205 --> 00:52:27,257
You don't love her anymore?

947
00:52:28,440 --> 00:52:29,797
Tommaso, I love Helena,

948
00:52:29,880 --> 00:52:31,557
but not the Helena that's with me now.

949
00:52:31,640 --> 00:52:33,007
There's only one Héléna,

950
00:52:33,090 --> 00:52:34,697
the one you're with right now.

951
00:52:34,780 --> 00:52:37,714
And it's no use being nice and sweet, believe me.

952
00:52:38,920 --> 00:52:40,148
You want my advice?

953
00:52:40,900 --> 00:52:43,185
Here's what Marquez would say.

954
00:52:43,268 --> 00:52:44,811
That's the old ending to my book.

955
00:52:48,320 --> 00:52:49,320
Yeah, but, uh.

956
00:52:50,137 --> 00:52:52,157
I can't tell her all this like this.

957
00:52:52,240 --> 00:52:54,068
You told me all of this yourself.

958
00:52:55,060 --> 00:52:56,834
How you've felt all these years.

959
00:52:57,485 --> 00:52:58,765
Or have you forgotten?

960
00:53:02,982 --> 00:53:05,314
Nina, would you be willing
to come to London with me?

961
00:53:06,930 --> 00:53:08,148
I don't know.

962
00:53:09,080 --> 00:53:11,908
But I think that's
that's up to the brass, not me.

963
00:53:19,257 --> 00:53:20,657
What if it were up to you?

964
00:53:20,740 --> 00:53:23,047
I recently started living together

965
00:53:23,130 --> 00:53:25,245
and I need to talk to my boyfriend.

966
00:53:30,285 --> 00:53:32,102
- Did I say something wrong?
- No, you didn't.

967
00:53:32,617 --> 00:53:33,707
How did you two meet?

968
00:53:33,790 --> 00:53:37,057
In one chat room, the site's support chat room.

969
00:53:37,140 --> 00:53:39,177
We wrote to each other,

970
00:53:39,828 --> 00:53:41,757
then we met,

971
00:53:41,840 --> 00:53:43,120
love at first sight.

972
00:53:44,880 --> 00:53:47,848
I hope you weren't chatting during work hours.

973
00:53:47,931 --> 00:53:48,931
No.

974
00:54:04,160 --> 00:54:05,371
A couple of chairs...

975
00:54:06,674 --> 00:54:07,894
On this side...

976
00:54:07,977 --> 00:54:10,720
I've never done anything
irrational in my entire life,

977
00:54:11,240 --> 00:54:12,800
but I'd like to meet you.

978
00:54:13,965 --> 00:54:16,897
One second, this is an important message,
and I have to-- I have to take this.

979
00:54:16,980 --> 00:54:18,437
Why do you want to see me?

980
00:54:18,520 --> 00:54:20,022
I don't even know what you look like.

981
00:54:20,910 --> 00:54:24,491
But I have a feeling that in a few days.
you've gotten to know me better than Tommaso.

982
00:54:25,130 --> 00:54:26,817
And you can also help me

983
00:54:26,900 --> 00:54:28,740
to find the right words
to break up with him.

984
00:54:34,380 --> 00:54:36,331
I could be one of those two.

985
00:54:38,091 --> 00:54:39,457
Or none of them.

986
00:54:39,540 --> 00:54:40,867
It doesn't matter.

987
00:54:40,950 --> 00:54:42,480
I'm willing to take the risk.

988
00:54:43,405 --> 00:54:44,405
What about you?

989
00:54:47,908 --> 00:54:50,257
6:00 p.m., Del Fico's Bar.

990
00:54:50,340 --> 00:54:51,474
How do you recognize me?

991
00:54:52,040 --> 00:54:53,287
You're as beautiful as a painting,

992
00:54:53,370 --> 00:54:55,622
with a nervous look on her face
and black nail polish.

993
00:55:08,685 --> 00:55:10,251
- Hey. (chuckles)
- Hey. (chuckles)

994
00:55:11,794 --> 00:55:13,307
Why are you dressed like that?

995
00:55:13,390 --> 00:55:15,782
Ah, nonsense, an aperitif with the bosses.

996
00:55:16,354 --> 00:55:18,217
I'll go straight to the restaurant from there, okay?

997
00:55:18,300 --> 00:55:20,045
Uh, okay. Zoya?

998
00:55:21,720 --> 00:55:22,877
Yes?

999
00:55:22,960 --> 00:55:23,960
Will you give me a hug?

1000
00:55:26,010 --> 00:55:27,108
What do you mean?

1001
00:55:28,068 --> 00:55:29,462
I mean, a hug.

1002
00:55:31,337 --> 00:55:33,782
Okay, but you don't ask that kind of thing.

1003
00:55:34,388 --> 00:55:35,531
It happens spontaneously.

1004
00:55:37,417 --> 00:55:38,417
But not you.

1005
00:55:39,862 --> 00:55:40,862
Not true.

1006
00:55:53,165 --> 00:55:54,365
I'm gonna go, it's getting late.

1007
00:56:12,834 --> 00:56:14,022
I'll have a gin and tonic!

1008
00:56:17,060 --> 00:56:18,060
Tom?

1009
00:56:19,050 --> 00:56:20,091
What are you doing here?

1010
00:56:24,468 --> 00:56:26,685
I invited Umberto over for a beer, but, uh.

1011
00:56:27,190 --> 00:56:28,720
But I didn't think you'd come here.

1012
00:56:29,560 --> 00:56:32,042
Wait a minute. I've got a sticking point.

1013
00:56:32,125 --> 00:56:33,125
Who are you writing to?

1014
00:56:33,771 --> 00:56:34,800
To the bosses.

1015
00:56:35,610 --> 00:56:37,085
Asked why they were late.

1016
00:56:41,930 --> 00:56:42,930
It's Umberto.

1017
00:56:42,960 --> 00:56:44,788
He's got an override, he's not coming.

1018
00:56:46,340 --> 00:56:48,377
- Well, I'll be off.
- Bye.

1019
00:56:52,845 --> 00:56:53,845
Zoya,

1020
00:56:55,005 --> 00:56:56,080
what's wrong with you?

1021
00:56:57,451 --> 00:57:01,508
You can't say "nothing"
or "problems at work."

1022
00:57:02,100 --> 00:57:04,948
Right, please, as always before.

1023
00:57:06,360 --> 00:57:08,811
I've been offered a move to London.

1024
00:57:09,720 --> 00:57:11,987
- It's a promotion, Tom.
- И?

1025
00:57:12,070 --> 00:57:14,022
- Can I get you anything?
- No, nothing, thank you.

1026
00:57:14,834 --> 00:57:16,240
Why didn't you say so before?

1027
00:57:17,000 --> 00:57:20,407
You've never taken much
interested in my work.

1028
00:57:20,490 --> 00:57:22,099
And you're mine,

1029
00:57:22,182 --> 00:57:23,851
you don't even know who I'm writing for.

1030
00:57:24,850 --> 00:57:27,005
But right now, it's about both of us.

1031
00:57:30,160 --> 00:57:31,457
Why didn't you tell me?

1032
00:57:31,540 --> 00:57:33,970
Because it's a decision
that I want to make.

1033
00:57:35,222 --> 00:57:36,222
alone.

1034
00:57:40,190 --> 00:57:42,137
And...have you decided?

1035
00:57:44,171 --> 00:57:45,200
Not yet.

1036
00:57:48,925 --> 00:57:49,942
Well, I'm gonna go.

1037
00:57:50,605 --> 00:57:51,657
Here comes the brass.

1038
00:57:52,370 --> 00:57:53,517
Tell him I said hi.

1039
00:57:53,600 --> 00:57:56,305
I'll see you right at Nello's, okay?

1040
00:57:56,388 --> 00:57:57,388
All right. Uh-huh.

1041
00:58:07,634 --> 00:58:08,742
You didn't come.

1042
00:58:10,742 --> 00:58:12,667
I saw you with a man and I left.

1043
00:58:12,750 --> 00:58:14,237
It's you, I'm sure of it.

1044
00:58:14,320 --> 00:58:15,520
I was with Tommaso.

1045
00:58:16,210 --> 00:58:17,817
Now I've seen you, it's all clear to me.

1046
00:58:17,900 --> 00:58:19,457
Don't delay.

1047
00:58:19,540 --> 00:58:21,528
You don't need my words anymore.

1048
00:58:21,611 --> 00:58:22,611
Drop it.

1049
00:58:36,777 --> 00:58:38,148
Héléna, listen to me.

1050
00:58:38,900 --> 00:58:40,457
Come on, come on, I'm listening.

1051
00:58:40,540 --> 00:58:43,394
I should tell you something,
but I thought I'd write.

1052
00:58:44,217 --> 00:58:47,939
"During those years, I felt
"abandoned, humiliated,

1053
00:58:48,022 --> 00:58:49,917
set aside like a trinket,

1054
00:58:50,000 --> 00:58:52,327
like an old glass ball
with snow inside.

1055
00:58:52,410 --> 00:58:54,137
I thought the snow wasn't there anymore.

1056
00:58:54,220 --> 00:58:56,868
But one day I turned the ball over,
and the snow started spinning like it used to.

1057
00:58:58,200 --> 00:59:00,342
That was the hundredth time
I've seen something without you.

1058
00:59:01,120 --> 00:59:03,627
I can't stand your late-night meetings anymore,

1059
00:59:03,710 --> 00:59:04,967
constant emergencies,

1060
00:59:05,050 --> 00:59:08,187
the way you get angry
when they change the road network.

1061
00:59:08,270 --> 00:59:11,447
But most of all, I can't
not be who I want to be anymore:

1062
00:59:11,530 --> 00:59:12,594
by a teacher,

1063
00:59:13,554 --> 00:59:14,554
husband,

1064
00:59:15,600 --> 00:59:16,600
a man."

1065
00:59:17,830 --> 00:59:19,348
Whose writing is this?

1066
00:59:23,180 --> 00:59:26,080
You didn't even listen to me
when I came to ask for a divorce.

1067
00:59:29,360 --> 00:59:30,891
I heard every word.

1068
00:59:32,090 --> 00:59:33,090
It doesn't look like it.

1069
00:59:34,890 --> 00:59:36,217
When have I ever humiliated you?

1070
00:59:37,230 --> 00:59:39,542
Who stopped you from teaching? Being a man?

1071
00:59:40,080 --> 00:59:41,577
"Snowballing" again?

1072
00:59:42,434 --> 00:59:43,714
Well, have I been listening well?

1073
00:59:44,230 --> 00:59:45,457
Not even the last sentence?

1074
00:59:45,540 --> 00:59:48,411
I'm a woman, Umberto,
I can do many things at once.

1075
00:59:49,870 --> 00:59:51,257
When we started living together,

1076
00:59:51,340 --> 00:59:53,617
you knew what I wanted to do.

1077
00:59:53,700 --> 00:59:55,505
Politics is my mission, Umberto.

1078
00:59:55,588 --> 00:59:58,454
It's one thing to go to a meeting,
to see "We loved each other so much."

1079
00:59:58,537 --> 00:59:59,574
to eat pork,

1080
00:59:59,657 --> 01:00:02,097
to discuss the society
that we leave to our children.

1081
01:00:02,180 --> 01:00:04,217
It's another thing
is to live a life of constant inactivity,

1082
01:00:04,300 --> 01:00:06,351
where's my moment of fame--
magazine cover photo,

1083
01:00:06,434 --> 01:00:07,517
where I fall off my bike!

1084
01:00:07,600 --> 01:00:11,267
With all of our city's problems.
do you care how you came out in the picture?

1085
01:00:11,350 --> 01:00:14,248
No, what I care about
that I go to the store with security,

1086
01:00:14,331 --> 01:00:16,387
who's judging me
that I bought a discount ham!

1087
01:00:16,470 --> 01:00:19,827
What worries me is that during your self-imposed isolation.
you were hardly ever home!

1088
01:00:19,910 --> 01:00:22,742
We're the only ones
who didn't stay home together during quarantine!

1089
01:00:29,050 --> 01:00:30,602
First of all, don't raise your voice at me.

1090
01:00:30,685 --> 01:00:32,357
- I didn't raise my voice.
- You're raising your voice!

1091
01:00:32,440 --> 01:00:33,587
And now you're stepping it up!

1092
01:00:33,670 --> 01:00:35,367
And, two, you have no idea,

1093
01:00:35,450 --> 01:00:37,167
that I've had to deal with
in that time.

1094
01:00:37,250 --> 01:00:39,162
What, am I, the mayor of Rome, going to sit at home?

1095
01:00:39,245 --> 01:00:41,587
- Do you realize what you're saying?
- Yes, I do.

1096
01:00:41,670 --> 01:00:43,477
I realize there's always a problem.

1097
01:00:43,560 --> 01:00:46,097
Years of formal dinners
where I ate poorly and ate little,

1098
01:00:46,180 --> 01:00:47,887
terrified of which fork to get,

1099
01:00:47,970 --> 01:00:50,307
scolded for pouring water
in the wrong cup.

1100
01:00:50,390 --> 01:00:53,059
Can't you see we've changed?
Everything has changed.

1101
01:00:53,142 --> 01:00:55,357
Don't be a child, Umberto.

1102
01:00:55,440 --> 01:00:57,337
So tell me, what exactly has changed?

1103
01:00:57,420 --> 01:01:00,517
- What's changed?
- Everything, Héléna, everything has changed, everything!

1104
01:01:00,600 --> 01:01:03,527
Now, we used to organize demonstrations
against the exploitation of the workers,

1105
01:01:03,610 --> 01:01:04,897
and now we have two Filipinos!

1106
01:01:04,980 --> 01:01:05,985
Formalized,

1107
01:01:06,068 --> 01:01:08,447
and we pay taxes, vacation pay,
13th paycheck, what's the big deal?

1108
01:01:08,530 --> 01:01:10,567
In that I want to give back to my students,

1109
01:01:10,650 --> 01:01:12,697
my car and my marriage!

1110
01:01:15,880 --> 01:01:17,440
You want your 20s back.

1111
01:01:19,005 --> 01:01:20,388
And that I can even understand.

1112
01:01:22,380 --> 01:01:23,562
I know I'm very busy,

1113
01:01:23,645 --> 01:01:25,470
but you can't
ask me to do that right now.

1114
01:01:26,491 --> 01:01:28,674
Wait a few months, we'll figure it out.

1115
01:01:29,725 --> 01:01:30,994
There are things like this,

1116
01:01:32,010 --> 01:01:33,847
that affect everyone.

1117
01:01:33,930 --> 01:01:35,797
And if you're betting our marriage

1118
01:01:35,880 --> 01:01:37,227
above the best interests of our city,

1119
01:01:37,310 --> 01:01:39,497
you're ungrateful and irresponsible.

1120
01:01:40,171 --> 01:01:41,565
A crisis of the party?

1121
01:01:42,628 --> 01:01:44,514
The interests of the city, Héléna?

1122
01:01:45,405 --> 01:01:47,851
You've completely lost your sense of proportion.

1123
01:01:50,285 --> 01:01:51,337
You don't love me anymore?

1124
01:01:56,022 --> 01:01:58,774
I'm no longer in love
a cold, formal lady,

1125
01:01:58,857 --> 01:02:00,137
that's standing in front of me.

1126
01:02:01,417 --> 01:02:03,782
Now sign my restraining order to keep you.

1127
01:02:12,040 --> 01:02:13,977
By the way, it's been an hour.

1128
01:02:15,222 --> 01:02:17,611
I should have borrowed Esther's
a Spanish frying pan.

1129
01:02:18,540 --> 01:02:19,974
A frying pan is like a frying pan.

1130
01:02:20,057 --> 01:02:23,307
No, "paella" is a special skillet,
not just the recipe.

1131
01:02:23,390 --> 01:02:25,257
The frying pan matters, Tom.

1132
01:02:26,340 --> 01:02:28,285
Okay, hand me two sheets of newspaper.

1133
01:02:30,834 --> 01:02:32,514
If you want, you can wait there.

1134
01:02:33,280 --> 01:02:34,927
That's not what we were going to do.

1135
01:02:35,010 --> 01:02:36,411
We decided it together.

1136
01:02:36,910 --> 01:02:39,257
Not all decisions are made together, it seems.

1137
01:02:39,340 --> 01:02:40,967
- Working in London, Tom, it's, uh.
- No, no, no.

1138
01:02:41,050 --> 01:02:42,050
Uh, hold on.

1139
01:02:43,000 --> 01:02:44,157
What do I have to look forward to?

1140
01:02:44,240 --> 01:02:45,862
Just to let the rice dry, okay?

1141
01:02:47,531 --> 01:02:48,531
All right. Uh-huh.

1142
01:02:49,645 --> 01:02:50,697
We'll wait.

1143
01:02:52,100 --> 01:02:53,360
How much did it come out to, baby?

1144
01:02:54,850 --> 01:02:56,342
You can't even be called baby?

1145
01:02:56,900 --> 01:02:58,837
Okay, let's go.

1146
01:02:58,920 --> 01:03:00,487
24 points.

1147
01:03:00,570 --> 01:03:01,727
24!

1148
01:03:01,810 --> 01:03:05,307
Guys, I'm sorry, but I'm afraid,
Spain won't get a prize tonight.

1149
01:03:05,390 --> 01:03:07,627
- The rice was a little overcooked.
- Yeah.

1150
01:03:07,710 --> 01:03:10,527
- The squid was a little tough.
- And the dessert was gross.

1151
01:03:10,610 --> 01:03:13,397
You don't say "disgusting."
they say "didn't like it."

1152
01:03:13,480 --> 01:03:15,714
Yeah, I didn't like him,
because he was mean.

1153
01:03:17,485 --> 01:03:19,987
We had a disagreement on the menu.

1154
01:03:20,070 --> 01:03:22,167
My fault, I was a little nervous.

1155
01:03:22,250 --> 01:03:24,305
Then, the frying pan is no good.

1156
01:03:24,388 --> 01:03:25,987
Attention!

1157
01:03:26,070 --> 01:03:28,067
Now it's the frying pan's fault!

1158
01:03:28,150 --> 01:03:29,727
Did the agitator fit?

1159
01:03:29,810 --> 01:03:31,447
Like when you lose at tennis.

1160
01:03:31,530 --> 01:03:33,187
It's always the racket's fault.

1161
01:03:33,270 --> 01:03:34,957
This is typical of Italians.

1162
01:03:35,040 --> 01:03:36,605
It's always someone else's fault.

1163
01:03:37,131 --> 01:03:38,422
Always!

1164
01:03:39,580 --> 01:03:40,674
Why so gloomy?

1165
01:03:42,130 --> 01:03:43,394
It's a game, right?

1166
01:04:00,971 --> 01:04:03,748
A high-pressure zone from northern Europe...

1167
01:04:05,040 --> 01:04:06,842
Tommaso, we need to talk.

1168
01:04:06,925 --> 01:04:08,837
- Check the readiness...
- We'll talk.

1169
01:04:08,920 --> 01:04:11,127
- Now that the cake--
- Turn it off, please.

1170
01:04:11,210 --> 01:04:13,474
You can sprinkle powdered sugar on top.....

1171
01:04:14,731 --> 01:04:15,760
You're welcome.

1172
01:04:26,040 --> 01:04:28,807
It's really hard for me to find the right words.

1173
01:04:28,890 --> 01:04:29,890
Don't pick it up.

1174
01:04:31,240 --> 01:04:32,240
It's all right.

1175
01:04:33,405 --> 01:04:35,147
It's very clear, Zoya.

1176
01:04:35,230 --> 01:04:36,837
It's been a long time coming.

1177
01:04:36,920 --> 01:04:40,068
I don't want to sit here and listen
your pity speech about how

1178
01:04:40,605 --> 01:04:42,434
that it's over between us.

1179
01:04:45,028 --> 01:04:46,028
I'm sorry.

1180
01:04:46,571 --> 01:04:47,571
Okay...

1181
01:04:50,430 --> 01:04:52,308
I don't know what's happening to me.

1182
01:04:52,880 --> 01:04:56,102
I assure you that I will always
I'll always be here for you, you know.

1183
01:05:01,497 --> 01:05:03,947
"I'll always be there for you, you know."

1184
01:05:04,030 --> 01:05:06,877
My God, you are so...corny.

1185
01:05:06,960 --> 01:05:08,037
Trite, Tom, why?

1186
01:05:08,120 --> 01:05:10,822
Tom! Tom! That's the navigator's name!

1187
01:05:16,068 --> 01:05:17,068
Tell me.

1188
01:05:18,800 --> 01:05:19,851
Is this about London?

1189
01:05:21,577 --> 01:05:22,925
Because of a lot of things...

1190
01:05:23,480 --> 01:05:25,600
I'm not sure about a lot of things anymore, Tom.

1191
01:05:27,140 --> 01:05:29,807
And I don't want to be held down by a relationship.

1192
01:05:29,890 --> 01:05:30,982
Who's holding you?

1193
01:05:31,588 --> 01:05:32,588
Я?

1194
01:05:33,211 --> 01:05:34,211
Id.

1195
01:05:34,980 --> 01:05:38,031
And I'm sorry I kept you for ten years
in this shitty town.

1196
01:05:38,114 --> 01:05:39,917
It's called ambition, Tom.

1197
01:05:40,000 --> 01:05:41,074
You don't know what it is.

1198
01:05:41,748 --> 01:05:43,851
Too bad, I thought you'd understand,

1199
01:05:45,280 --> 01:05:46,597
But I guess not.

1200
01:05:46,680 --> 01:05:48,868
You're leaving me, what's there to understand?

1201
01:05:50,030 --> 01:05:51,188
That I feel bad, too.

1202
01:05:51,730 --> 01:05:53,939
If you want, I'll caress you, huh?

1203
01:05:54,022 --> 01:05:55,327
Do you want a caress?

1204
01:05:55,410 --> 01:05:56,548
Don't be a child.

1205
01:05:57,390 --> 01:05:58,648
You don't get it.

1206
01:05:58,731 --> 01:06:00,114
I never understand anything.

1207
01:06:00,880 --> 01:06:03,797
You always understand everything,
and the rest of the world doesn't.

1208
01:06:03,880 --> 01:06:06,914
You know, my friends can't stand you,
and you haven't even noticed?

1209
01:06:07,668 --> 01:06:09,717
Get off your heels once in a while

1210
01:06:09,800 --> 01:06:12,251
and ask what people really think of you.

1211
01:06:13,410 --> 01:06:14,737
I don't get it.

1212
01:06:14,820 --> 01:06:17,451
You know... fine.

1213
01:06:19,554 --> 01:06:20,765
- Tommaso...
- Zoya.

1214
01:06:23,817 --> 01:06:24,868
Go to hell.

1215
01:07:07,370 --> 01:07:09,208
- Hey.
- How's it going? Everything okay?

1216
01:07:09,291 --> 01:07:10,291
Yes.

1217
01:07:10,742 --> 01:07:12,257
I'll stay with you for a few days.

1218
01:07:12,340 --> 01:07:13,340
Uh, sure.

1219
01:07:15,260 --> 01:07:16,308
Got any wine?

1220
01:07:17,620 --> 01:07:19,048
At 1:30 in the morning?

1221
01:07:19,131 --> 01:07:20,131
What are we drinking to?

1222
01:07:20,550 --> 01:07:21,828
To my promotion.

1223
01:07:22,411 --> 01:07:23,411
Assigned?

1224
01:07:24,530 --> 01:07:25,817
They'll announce it tomorrow.

1225
01:07:26,620 --> 01:07:28,217
Is it possible to celebrate earlier?

1226
01:07:29,350 --> 01:07:31,097
No, no, I'm not superstitious.

1227
01:07:36,760 --> 01:07:37,977
I left Tommaso.

1228
01:07:50,140 --> 01:07:52,968
TOMMASO ROSSO
"MEANS NEVER"

1229
01:07:53,051 --> 01:07:55,980
"TOUCHING FINALE"

1230
01:07:56,891 --> 01:07:58,237
No tears.

1231
01:07:58,320 --> 01:07:59,320
It happens.

1232
01:07:59,960 --> 01:08:01,920
It's in the nature of things.

1233
01:08:03,085 --> 01:08:04,971
You change and you make choices.

1234
01:08:05,870 --> 01:08:07,947
And when you break up, the one who leaves,

1235
01:08:08,030 --> 01:08:10,008
and has to give explanations.

1236
01:08:10,091 --> 01:08:11,091
I know,

1237
01:08:11,600 --> 01:08:13,782
but that's the kind of rhetoric that means.

1238
01:08:14,460 --> 01:08:15,462
I won't.

1239
01:08:16,680 --> 01:08:18,587
On the contrary, I'll smile.

1240
01:08:18,670 --> 01:08:19,805
Let's do it the other way around.

1241
01:08:20,640 --> 01:08:21,931
You tell me.

1242
01:08:22,640 --> 01:08:26,037
I want to know
what you think of me, the truth.

1243
01:08:26,120 --> 01:08:27,317
Without any pathos.

1244
01:08:27,400 --> 01:08:29,120
Don't worry, I can't fire you.

1245
01:08:29,870 --> 01:08:30,870
Nina?

1246
01:08:31,290 --> 01:08:33,611
No, nothing comes to mind.

1247
01:08:34,530 --> 01:08:35,530
Virginia?

1248
01:08:37,640 --> 01:08:38,640
Marco?

1249
01:08:39,800 --> 01:08:41,520
Okay, I don't insist.

1250
01:08:42,090 --> 01:08:44,922
Ah, Nina, it came to me in the general newsletter:

1251
01:08:45,005 --> 01:08:47,177
"There's a corporate party tonight."

1252
01:08:47,260 --> 01:08:48,922
What's going to happen tonight?

1253
01:08:49,005 --> 01:08:52,305
Well, it's a party at the same establishment.....

1254
01:08:52,388 --> 01:08:53,851
It came to you by mistake.

1255
01:08:54,990 --> 01:08:57,485
If you come over, we can have a drink together.

1256
01:08:58,550 --> 01:09:00,387
- A drink?
- Why don't you--

1257
01:09:00,470 --> 01:09:01,737
Well done, Tommaso.

1258
01:09:04,148 --> 01:09:06,537
Bad news always comes in pairs.

1259
01:09:06,620 --> 01:09:08,947
Okay, this is for her.

1260
01:09:09,030 --> 01:09:10,971
Give it to her when she comes to get her stuff.

1261
01:09:11,710 --> 01:09:14,454
- Anyway, Tommaso, I've read it.
- Yes.

1262
01:09:14,537 --> 01:09:15,714
Shall I tell you the truth?

1263
01:09:16,217 --> 01:09:17,927
It's kind of boring,

1264
01:09:18,010 --> 01:09:20,948
except for the finale, which is just good!

1265
01:09:22,350 --> 01:09:24,357
Since you're here, will you have lunch with us?

1266
01:09:24,440 --> 01:09:27,187
Friday, Maria is making onion soup.

1267
01:09:27,270 --> 01:09:30,751
Yeah, thanks, but it's, uh.
not exactly my favorite dish.

1268
01:09:30,834 --> 01:09:32,137
And it's not mine.

1269
01:09:32,220 --> 01:09:35,097
What's more, it disgusts me.

1270
01:09:35,180 --> 01:09:37,457
But she's been brewing it since
since we got engaged.

1271
01:09:37,540 --> 01:09:40,087
And I haven't dared to tell her that since 1969,

1272
01:09:40,170 --> 01:09:43,325
and now I have to pay that tax for 50 years.

1273
01:09:53,302 --> 01:09:55,347
I escaped, the guards didn't see me.

1274
01:09:55,430 --> 01:09:57,597
Suddenly I wanted to see you like I used to,

1275
01:09:57,680 --> 01:09:58,742
alone with you.

1276
01:09:59,920 --> 01:10:01,897
And I missed that car.

1277
01:10:01,980 --> 01:10:05,828
It's without an accelerant, if we get caught,
you'll lose six or seven percent of the vote.

1278
01:10:07,577 --> 01:10:08,674
Do you remember when...

1279
01:10:09,290 --> 01:10:12,354
When we drove it to Turin
to the De André concert?

1280
01:10:13,005 --> 01:10:15,337
September 18, 1991.

1281
01:10:16,445 --> 01:10:18,080
I got sick on the first song.

1282
01:10:19,840 --> 01:10:22,788
I've always loved you,

1283
01:10:23,600 --> 01:10:26,347
I never loved you...

1284
01:10:26,430 --> 01:10:29,077
