1785
01:37:49,314 --> 01:37:50,487
Where to?

1786
01:37:50,570 --> 01:37:52,445
To the hospital in case I broke your nose?

1787
01:37:54,530 --> 01:37:55,530
Let's go.

1788
01:37:58,217 --> 01:38:02,097
A press conference has been urgently called,
to be held at City Hall.

1789
01:38:02,180 --> 01:38:04,022
She recognized Marquez as me.

1790
01:38:05,780 --> 01:38:07,859
We threw all the plates and glasses
all the plates and glasses,

1791
01:38:07,942 --> 01:38:09,071
unbroken in ten years.

1792
01:38:09,154 --> 01:38:11,539
...Lately, our mayor hasn't....

1793
01:38:11,622 --> 01:38:13,702
Damn, it's hard to break up!

1794
01:38:14,914 --> 01:38:16,017
It's really hard.

1795
01:38:16,100 --> 01:38:19,277
...they never miss an opportunity
to criticize her work,

1796
01:38:19,360 --> 01:38:22,007
as we can hear in this interview.

1797
01:38:22,090 --> 01:38:25,137
How can a woman
who can't bring her family together,

1798
01:38:25,220 --> 01:38:26,777
to rally the entire city of Rome?

1799
01:38:26,860 --> 01:38:28,160
I don't know, you tell me!

1800
01:38:28,830 --> 01:38:32,107
It was a statement by the secretary of the Party
of the New Italian Renaissance,

1801
01:38:32,190 --> 01:38:34,240
made a few minutes
before the conference began...

1802
01:38:42,605 --> 01:38:44,822
Umberto, where the hell are we?

1803
01:38:50,765 --> 01:38:51,765
But...

1804
01:38:52,360 --> 01:38:53,474
There he is, she's here...

1805
01:39:07,210 --> 01:39:09,557
Hello, welcome, everyone.

1806
01:39:09,640 --> 01:39:10,651
Thank you for being here.

1807
01:39:11,154 --> 01:39:13,507
Without getting too personal,

1808
01:39:13,590 --> 01:39:17,779
I absolutely must
to take responsibility for the city,

1809
01:39:17,862 --> 01:39:20,419
who deserves 100% of my energy,

1810
01:39:20,502 --> 01:39:23,268
of my time and my devotion.

1811
01:39:24,230 --> 01:39:26,891
But the people I care about deserve the same.

1812
01:39:28,690 --> 01:39:29,690
So, uh,

1813
01:39:31,090 --> 01:39:33,954
Having discussed it with my party and....

1814
01:39:34,537 --> 01:39:35,777
and after...

1815
01:39:35,860 --> 01:39:37,957
a long discussion with my family....

1816
01:39:38,040 --> 01:39:39,040
Wait!

1817
01:39:47,314 --> 01:39:50,605
I never believed that someone like you
could fall in love with someone like me.

1818
01:39:51,600 --> 01:39:53,382
Remember what you were like when you were 25?

1819
01:39:54,630 --> 01:39:56,527
As beautiful as she is now.

1820
01:39:56,610 --> 01:39:58,347
And I was fat, too,

1821
01:39:58,430 --> 01:40:01,047
almost as fat as he is now.

1822
01:40:01,130 --> 01:40:03,794
So I thought:
"Okay, she's gonna leave me someday."

1823
01:40:04,590 --> 01:40:06,800
The more you grew, the fatter I got.

1824
01:40:07,360 --> 01:40:11,057
I thought I was
an example of nonconformity for you,

1825
01:40:11,140 --> 01:40:13,887
to show that you're different.

1826
01:40:13,970 --> 01:40:17,557
But you married me, and I thought:
"Now she's gonna leave me."

1827
01:40:17,640 --> 01:40:21,097
Then Matilda was born,
and I thought, "He's going to quit now."

1828
01:40:21,657 --> 01:40:23,905
Then there's the secretary, the counselor,

1829
01:40:23,988 --> 01:40:25,587
and now head of the city of Rome.

1830
01:40:25,670 --> 01:40:28,911
And every time I thought, "She's going to leave me."

1831
01:40:28,994 --> 01:40:30,320
But since you didn't leave me,

1832
01:40:31,622 --> 01:40:33,097
I've decided to leave you on my own.

1833
01:40:34,171 --> 01:40:36,137
I exaggerated your shortcomings,

1834
01:40:36,220 --> 01:40:37,794
to justify your fear.

1835
01:40:39,005 --> 01:40:42,137
But instead of retreating,
I had to step forward:

1836
01:40:42,220 --> 01:40:43,220
to be with you.

1837
01:40:43,730 --> 01:40:47,317
I mean, millions of women in history
have done so, for centuries.

1838
01:40:47,400 --> 01:40:49,637
And they had to do that,
they had no choice.

1839
01:40:49,720 --> 01:40:51,167
Can I, a man,

1840
01:40:51,250 --> 01:40:54,308
to live like this for 20 years
or a couple terms in office?

1841
01:40:55,954 --> 01:40:57,028
I think so.

1842
01:40:58,285 --> 01:40:59,707
So, Héléna,

1843
01:40:59,790 --> 01:41:02,125
come home with this ribbon.

1844
01:41:09,817 --> 01:41:13,057
Usually after such a passionate speech.

1845
01:41:13,140 --> 01:41:15,448
the crowd stands up and, uh.

1846
01:41:15,531 --> 01:41:17,131
and applauds, but, uh.

1847
01:41:18,680 --> 01:41:21,905
Get out of here now, please,
this is an official press conference,

1848
01:41:21,988 --> 01:41:23,428
not an American movie.

1849
01:41:25,211 --> 01:41:26,211
I'm sorry...

1850
01:41:35,565 --> 01:41:36,565
Uh, excuse me.

1851
01:41:37,382 --> 01:41:39,577
- What's going on?
- I don't understand.

1852
01:41:43,668 --> 01:41:44,668
Umberto!

1853
01:41:47,950 --> 01:41:49,028
Take off your glasses.

1854
01:41:54,040 --> 01:41:56,491
You were being disgusting, as usual.

1855
01:41:58,571 --> 01:42:00,091
But I recognize you now.

1856
01:42:08,971 --> 01:42:11,157
- I'll see you at dinner.
- What dinner?

1857
01:42:11,240 --> 01:42:13,747
It's gonna be a long time,
I'm gonna be asked a million questions.

1858
01:42:13,830 --> 01:42:15,897
Okay, we'll have breakfast together tomorrow.

1859
01:42:15,980 --> 01:42:17,459
No, I'll leave early tomorrow,

1860
01:42:17,542 --> 01:42:19,277
should be at the construction site of the third subway line.

1861
01:42:19,360 --> 01:42:21,242
The work got up there, they found two amphorae.

1862
01:42:21,325 --> 01:42:23,057
That's a shame. Well, I'll see you when you get back.

1863
01:42:23,140 --> 01:42:25,497
And on Wednesday morning.
I'm driving to Brussels at dawn

1864
01:42:25,580 --> 01:42:27,737
on the Committee of European Capitals of Culture.

1865
01:42:27,820 --> 01:42:29,428
- I must--
- Save Rome, I know.

1866
01:42:30,045 --> 01:42:31,045
I'll give it a try.

1867
01:42:31,630 --> 01:42:32,630
I'll be waiting.

1868
01:42:33,234 --> 01:42:34,277
But!

1869
01:42:34,360 --> 01:42:35,665
Dinner will get cold,

1870
01:42:35,748 --> 01:42:37,894
and Matilda and I will make a scene for you
a scene for being late,

1871
01:42:37,977 --> 01:42:40,917
and you're not gonna say anything,
because there's more of us.

1872
01:42:41,000 --> 01:42:42,560
And at home, we're in charge.

1873
01:42:43,817 --> 01:42:44,817
Id.

1874
01:42:45,222 --> 01:42:47,062
I'll be in stiff opposition,

1875
01:42:47,610 --> 01:42:49,062
but responsibly!

1876
01:42:49,954 --> 01:42:51,447
- Smile.
- Why?

1877
01:42:51,530 --> 01:42:52,685
There are photographers here.

1878
01:42:58,240 --> 01:42:59,782
Nina, can you call, uh.

1879
01:43:07,710 --> 01:43:08,710
Tommaso?

1880
01:43:32,060 --> 01:43:33,637
Here's a new report.

1881
01:43:33,720 --> 01:43:35,680
Three percent, not six percent.

1882
01:43:37,280 --> 01:43:39,345
Excuse us for just then.

1883
01:43:39,428 --> 01:43:42,068
And thanks from everyone for the bonus.

1884
01:43:42,560 --> 01:43:45,699
It's a gift from us,

1885
01:43:45,782 --> 01:43:46,891
for good luck.

1886
01:43:47,668 --> 01:43:48,777
100 yen...

1887
01:43:50,125 --> 01:43:51,387
Thank you.

1888
01:43:51,470 --> 01:43:52,470
Come on.

1889
01:43:52,870 --> 01:43:55,627
Here's to the new senior manager
of the London branch.

1890
01:43:55,710 --> 01:43:56,710
Momentum.

1891
01:43:57,760 --> 01:44:01,402
First, I want to hug each and every one of you,

1892
01:44:01,485 --> 01:44:02,571
bitches.

1893
01:44:12,182 --> 01:44:13,657
Now you know the whole story.

1894
01:44:13,740 --> 01:44:17,245
Mother of God, you were flirting
with Gabriel Garcia Marquez!

1895
01:44:18,020 --> 01:44:19,108
He took me...

1896
01:44:19,780 --> 01:44:21,619
He knew what to say, asshole!

1897
01:44:21,702 --> 01:44:22,702
You betcha!

1898
01:44:23,657 --> 01:44:26,948
So, basically.
you fell in love with Tommaso?

1899
01:44:28,020 --> 01:44:30,148
- He didn't choose the wine.
- What do you mean?

1900
01:44:31,965 --> 01:44:33,665
The first time we went out together,

1901
01:44:33,748 --> 01:44:35,287
we were at a wine bar.

1902
01:44:35,370 --> 01:44:37,965
Tommaso says to me:
"Take your pick, I don't care."

1903
01:44:38,697 --> 01:44:40,537
Never happened,

1904
01:44:40,620 --> 01:44:42,628
so a man doesn't pick out my wine.

1905
01:44:43,200 --> 01:44:45,367
Oddly enough, this one...

1906
01:44:45,450 --> 01:44:49,267
his relaxed nature
in any situation, I liked it.

1907
01:44:49,350 --> 01:44:51,379
Always in jeans, always in a sweatshirt,

1908
01:44:51,462 --> 01:44:53,357
even at your wedding, remember?

1909
01:44:53,440 --> 01:44:55,905
How will I forget? He ruined all the pictures.

1910
01:44:55,988 --> 01:44:57,937
And the way he said my name:

1911
01:44:58,020 --> 01:45:00,205
"N-Zoya, N-Zoya..."

1912
01:45:02,297 --> 01:45:03,725
It was horrible...

1913
01:45:05,462 --> 01:45:06,817
But it made me happy.

1914
01:45:06,900 --> 01:45:09,414
Zoé, you know, that's exactly what it is,

1915
01:45:09,497 --> 01:45:11,188
that you hated about him.

1916
01:45:26,731 --> 01:45:28,077
Hey, Marquez.

1917
01:45:28,160 --> 01:45:30,437
I wanted to ask you
one last favor.

1918
01:45:30,520 --> 01:45:31,874
I'd like to see Tommaso.

1919
01:45:32,450 --> 01:45:35,691
Where we met, on the Sisto Bridge.

1920
01:45:36,182 --> 01:45:37,542
It's our anniversary.

1921
01:45:38,251 --> 01:45:39,251
Am I right?

1922
01:45:44,331 --> 01:45:46,137
It's not about whether you're right or wrong.

1923
01:45:46,994 --> 01:45:48,651
I don't know if he'll agree.

1924
01:46:53,190 --> 01:46:54,437
Did you pack a suitcase?

1925
01:46:54,520 --> 01:46:55,520
The essentials.

1926
01:46:55,600 --> 01:46:58,207
I don't like to bring a lot of stuff with me.

1927
01:46:58,290 --> 01:46:59,290
I know.

1928
01:47:00,440 --> 01:47:01,668
What happened to your nose?

1929
01:47:02,982 --> 01:47:04,925
Well, let's say it's all Marquez.

1930
01:47:06,628 --> 01:47:08,365
- Are you okay?
- I'm not.

1931
01:47:10,422 --> 01:47:11,554
No, it's not.

1932
01:47:12,457 --> 01:47:15,600
But you have to answer:
"I'm fine, thank you. And you?"

1933
01:47:17,108 --> 01:47:18,480
I feel weird.

1934
01:47:19,634 --> 01:47:21,407
I don't know what I want.

1935
01:47:21,490 --> 01:47:22,525
Do you want to...

1936
01:47:23,060 --> 01:47:24,842
who drives a car with a tie on.

1937
01:47:24,925 --> 01:47:26,865
and listening to happy music,

1938
01:47:26,948 --> 01:47:29,577
writes novels with happy endings

1939
01:47:29,660 --> 01:47:31,965
without throwing her hair in the sink.

1940
01:47:33,380 --> 01:47:35,779
Tell me why, if I left you,

1941
01:47:35,862 --> 01:47:37,617
it makes me feel bad for some reason,

1942
01:47:37,700 --> 01:47:39,920
and you're like light and carefree?

1943
01:47:42,068 --> 01:47:44,537
I think it's because I'm desperate, Zoe.

1944
01:47:45,690 --> 01:47:49,554
So much for "joking" as usual.

1945
01:47:52,022 --> 01:47:53,325
Why would you want to see me?

1946
01:47:54,690 --> 01:47:57,622
Because it's not true
that we only had dinner at the restaurant.

1947
01:47:58,914 --> 01:48:00,662
We traveled,

1948
01:48:02,020 --> 01:48:03,771
we laughed a lot, Tom.

1949
01:48:04,457 --> 01:48:06,577
You're the person
who made me laugh the most

1950
01:48:06,660 --> 01:48:08,034
in my life.

1951
01:48:09,714 --> 01:48:12,537
We saved a lot of money
on broken plates.

1952
01:48:15,450 --> 01:48:18,045
And we made love less often than everyone else,

1953
01:48:19,210 --> 01:48:20,662
but a lot better than everyone else.

1954
01:48:21,348 --> 01:48:22,560
And three with two minuses?

1955
01:48:23,600 --> 01:48:26,057
Well, it's a weighted average.

1956
01:48:26,140 --> 01:48:28,117
As opposed to the arithmetic mean,

1957
01:48:28,200 --> 01:48:30,240
every number counts as more than just a number,

1958
01:48:30,810 --> 01:48:32,627
but it also carries a certain weight,

1959
01:48:32,710 --> 01:48:34,977
its importance, which affects the calculation.

1960
01:48:35,060 --> 01:48:36,080
You got it?

1961
01:48:37,462 --> 01:48:38,582
I realized that...

1962
01:48:39,250 --> 01:48:42,171
you always have
a genius way of looking at things, Zoe.

1963
01:48:43,062 --> 01:48:44,062
You see?

1964
01:48:44,440 --> 01:48:46,125
I've learned when I don't have to anymore.

1965
01:48:48,262 --> 01:48:49,417
Come with me.

1966
01:48:49,500 --> 01:48:50,662
We want to...

1967
01:48:51,714 --> 01:48:53,037
too different, Zoya.

1968
01:48:53,120 --> 01:48:54,008
Let's give it a try.

1969
01:48:54,091 --> 01:48:55,987
I've tried all these months,

1970
01:48:56,070 --> 01:48:57,451
but it didn't work out.

1971
01:48:58,860 --> 01:49:00,742
And so I'm not me anymore.

1972
01:49:01,771 --> 01:49:04,347
I'm... embarrassed.

1973
01:49:04,430 --> 01:49:07,547
I still don't like to drive,
I like sad music.

1974
01:49:07,630 --> 01:49:08,868
and sad endings.

1975
01:49:11,554 --> 01:49:13,062
And it's nobody's fault.

1976
01:49:15,700 --> 01:49:16,700
It happens.

1977
01:49:18,011 --> 01:49:20,148
If that's the case, why am I not happy?

1978
01:49:21,200 --> 01:49:22,200
Why?

1979
01:49:22,580 --> 01:49:25,371
Because the thought
of leaving without you makes me sad.

1980
01:49:26,920 --> 01:49:28,354
Incredibly sad.

1981
01:49:30,000 --> 01:49:31,565
I could come with you.

1982
01:49:34,011 --> 01:49:36,034
But what if I asked you to stay?

1983
01:49:50,685 --> 01:49:51,685
All right. Uh-huh.

1984
01:49:52,605 --> 01:49:54,762
Okay, I'll stay with you.

1985
01:49:54,845 --> 01:49:56,388
- Uh-huh?
- Yeah.

1986
01:49:57,110 --> 01:49:58,937
And when are you going to give me a hard time about it?

1987
01:50:00,845 --> 01:50:02,491
How soon we have each other...

1988
01:50:03,222 --> 01:50:04,377
hate?

1989
01:50:06,697 --> 01:50:08,320
And I don't want to hate you, Zoya.

1990
01:50:10,182 --> 01:50:12,662
I realized I wanted to be with you.

1991
01:50:14,500 --> 01:50:15,851
You don't want to be with me.

1992
01:50:17,580 --> 01:50:19,645
You're afraid of being without me.

1993
01:50:30,297 --> 01:50:31,428
Will you do me a favor?

1994
01:50:32,830 --> 01:50:35,725
Can you say that corny phrase?

1995
01:50:37,620 --> 01:50:38,891
It's a good place to be right now.

1996
01:50:44,354 --> 01:50:46,354
I'll always be there for you, you know.

1997
01:51:08,697 --> 01:51:14,520
ROMAN BREAKUPS

1998
01:51:39,337 --> 01:51:40,507
Good evening.

1999
01:51:40,590 --> 01:51:41,590
Are you two together?

2000
01:51:46,880 --> 01:51:47,880
- Uh, no.
- Uh, no.
